WEBVTT

00:01.083 --> 00:03.083
(Phone ringing, papers rustle)

00:03.083 --> 00:04.916
- Oh great, um, these, the
contracts are in triplicate,

00:04.916 --> 00:07.208
ready for Mr. Galvin to sign.
Thank you.

00:07.208 --> 00:09.958
(Phone rings)
Julianne Giacomelli's office.

00:09.958 --> 00:12.250
Uh-huh.

00:12.250 --> 00:13.958
Spencer. Rush delivery
to New York. Thanks.

00:13.958 --> 00:15.583
We've already canceled.

00:15.583 --> 00:17.125
If Deepak Chopra is
not gonna be there

00:17.125 --> 00:18.583
than she's not gonna be there.
Okay, great.

00:18.583 --> 00:20.291
(Phones ringing)

00:20.291 --> 00:23.166
Oh, more? 'Cause there is
no room on my desk.

00:23.166 --> 00:24.541
Remember that little
fishing boat

00:24.541 --> 00:26.041
from "The Perfect Storm"?

00:26.041 --> 00:27.958
How it climbed up
that endless wave,

00:27.958 --> 00:29.625
hoping to reach the top

00:29.625 --> 00:31.708
and cruise down
the other side to safety?

00:31.708 --> 00:33.250
That's me.

00:33.250 --> 00:34.708
Okay, good. Um, these are good
to go.

00:34.708 --> 00:36.333
I just corrected some typos
in paragraph four.

00:36.333 --> 00:38.791
Okay, thank you.
(Phones ring, overwhelmed moan)

00:38.791 --> 00:40.333
But just like that
fishing boat...

00:40.333 --> 00:42.875
I can't seem to quite
crest the wave.

00:42.875 --> 00:44.875
Julianne Giacomelli's office.
Ryan: Hey, I'm back.

00:44.875 --> 00:46.333
Would you believe me
if I told you

00:46.333 --> 00:48.916
the national dish of Ecuador
is guinea pig?

00:48.916 --> 00:51.458
- Uh, hey Ryan, I'm sorry,
this really isn't a good time.

00:51.458 --> 00:52.416
I'm just-I'm buried in work.

00:52.416 --> 00:54.375
- All right this won't take
long. I just wanted to see

00:54.375 --> 00:56.125
if we can shift our plans
from tonight to tomorrow night.

00:56.125 --> 00:57.250
- Uh, why, did something
come up?

00:57.250 --> 00:58.916
- Josh called, and he can only
get together tonight.

00:58.916 --> 01:00.791
Erica: Oh.

01:00.791 --> 01:02.250
- But tomorrow night,
I promise, I'm all yours.

01:02.250 --> 01:05.250
Dinner, movie, roast guinea
pig, you name it.

01:05.250 --> 01:07.125
Okay, sure. I guess. Um...

01:08.750 --> 01:10.125
Look, is this gonna be
a problem?

01:10.125 --> 01:12.666
- No.
- Ryan, my sister hates me.

01:12.666 --> 01:14.083
It's not a stretch to imagine
that her husband

01:14.083 --> 01:16.666
isn't exactly thrilled that
we're together.

01:16.666 --> 01:18.625
- That's his deal.
And, for what it's worth,

01:18.625 --> 01:20.625
this whole thing between you
and your sister?

01:20.625 --> 01:23.125
I'm sure it'll blow over.
- I hope so. Bye.

01:23.125 --> 01:24.875
- I'd hate to keep you from
planning your social life,

01:24.875 --> 01:26.833
I just thought maybe you could,
you know, do your job.

01:26.833 --> 01:29.083
- I am. Uh, what do you need?

01:29.083 --> 01:31.625
- Uh, the launch strategy file
for Mark Stahl's book,
five minutes ago.

01:31.625 --> 01:33.208
- Okay, well, when does he
want to hear it?

01:33.208 --> 01:34.500
- Now. And you're helping
with the pitch,

01:34.500 --> 01:36.083
So, come on, it's game time.

01:36.083 --> 01:38.041
- Whoa, we're launching
a book that Stahl hasn't
even written yet?

01:38.041 --> 01:39.750
I mean, we don't even
have the chapters?

01:39.750 --> 01:40.833
- Yes, Erica, we do have them.

01:40.833 --> 01:42.750
They're in editing.

01:42.750 --> 01:44.875
Show me your poker face.

01:44.875 --> 01:48.291
(Phones ringing)

01:48.291 --> 01:50.958
Oh, God, help us.

01:50.958 --> 01:52.375
We think that this book
is perfect

01:52.375 --> 01:54.125
for the business
traveler market.

01:54.125 --> 01:56.791
- We think?
Erica: We know.

01:56.791 --> 01:58.291
Uh, the research backs it up.

01:58.291 --> 02:00.291
Young professionals,
they love self-help books

02:00.291 --> 02:03.083
with a dash of schadenfreude
thrown in.

02:03.083 --> 02:04.958
- (Clears throat) We'll focus
on the tell-all angle.

02:04.958 --> 02:06.791
- Which we leverage
for the talk shows.

02:06.791 --> 02:08.750
- All for a major
pre-Christmas launch.

02:08.750 --> 02:10.791
- And with a cover this good?

02:10.791 --> 02:13.875
We think it'll grab
everyone's eye.

02:13.875 --> 02:15.750
- Hmm. Bring it here.

02:18.875 --> 02:21.000
Oh.

02:21.000 --> 02:24.166
I'm liking this. It's grabby.

02:24.166 --> 02:25.583
I'll take the chapters home
tonight,

02:25.583 --> 02:27.125
and send you my notes
in the morning.

02:27.125 --> 02:29.166
- Oh, actually, Frank, um...
we do have three chapters,

02:29.166 --> 02:31.166
but they're still very...

02:31.166 --> 02:33.000
- Raw.
- Raw.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.208
- I don't need 'em prettied up.
I wanna see what I'm paying for.

02:35.208 --> 02:36.541
Who's got them right now?

02:36.541 --> 02:38.000
- Oh, um...

02:38.000 --> 02:40.333
- Who? Um... Dory.

02:40.333 --> 02:41.916
- Dory is editing "The history
of coffee".

02:41.916 --> 02:44.250
I just spoke to her.

02:44.250 --> 02:46.916
Stop bullshitting me,
and get me something to read!

02:46.916 --> 02:48.250
Today!

02:53.083 --> 02:54.500
Erica: So, if you're
in the water

02:54.500 --> 02:55.875
and the waves keep
smacking you down,

02:55.875 --> 02:57.208
what do you do?

02:58.833 --> 03:01.000
Sometimes you manage
to soldier on,

03:01.000 --> 03:03.708
Clutch the steering wheel
and face the storm.

03:03.708 --> 03:05.916
- Dory?

03:05.916 --> 03:08.416
Everyone knows she's editing
the freaking coffee book.

03:08.416 --> 03:10.416
- Julianne, I'm sorry.
I just I-I thought that--

03:10.416 --> 03:12.875
- Oh, well you won't be doing
that again, will you?

03:12.875 --> 03:14.958
If we don't have pages
by end of day,

03:14.958 --> 03:17.041
Galvin will have me
thrown out that window

03:17.041 --> 03:19.291
and I'll throw you first
to break my fall.

03:19.291 --> 03:21.083
Believe me.
- I do.

03:21.083 --> 03:23.666
- Then get me pages.

03:24.125 --> 03:25.625
Okay.

03:25.625 --> 03:27.916
(Phones ringing)

03:32.208 --> 03:33.666
Erica: While other times,

03:33.666 --> 03:35.958
you look around and see
the situation clearly.

03:35.958 --> 03:38.833
That ultimately you're going
to drown.

03:42.875 --> 03:52.791
♪ ♪

03:52.791 --> 03:55.208
♪ It's clearer inside of me ♪

03:55.208 --> 03:57.916
♪ Who I will always be ♪

03:57.916 --> 04:00.291
♪ Open me up to my heart ♪

04:02.958 --> 04:05.458
♪ Feels like I'm seeing
in the dark ♪

04:05.458 --> 04:08.083
♪ Waking me up to my heart ♪

04:08.083 --> 04:10.333
♪ To do it all over ♪

04:10.333 --> 04:12.791
♪ Again and again ♪

04:12.791 --> 04:15.208
♪ Until the end ♪

04:15.208 --> 04:17.958
♪ The sum of my dreams ♪

04:17.958 --> 04:20.666
♪ And everything
I ever wanted to be ♪

04:23.791 --> 04:25.208
Gary: When I said let's have
lunch,

04:25.208 --> 04:26.958
I meant let's have lunch
in a restaurant.

04:26.958 --> 04:28.375
Erica: No time. Besides,
standing up eating,

04:28.375 --> 04:30.458
I think it's better
for digestion, anyway.

04:30.458 --> 04:32.875
- You know what I want
to talk to you about.

04:32.875 --> 04:34.708
- Dad, please, I can't today.

04:34.708 --> 04:36.250
- You know how hard it is,

04:36.250 --> 04:38.125
to have my two daughters
not speaking to each other?

04:38.125 --> 04:39.500
- Okay, well, try being
one of the daughters.

04:39.500 --> 04:41.083
I mean, she won't return
my calls.

04:41.083 --> 04:43.833
I've tried leaving messages,
I've tried email, I mean...

04:43.833 --> 04:45.375
I've tried, but at a certain
point, dad,

04:45.375 --> 04:47.250
you just, you gotta say
enough is enough.

04:47.250 --> 04:48.708
- So, you're giving up
on your sister.

04:48.708 --> 04:50.166
Is that it?

04:50.166 --> 04:53.041
- I really miss her.

04:53.041 --> 04:55.708
- I know. What can I do?

04:55.708 --> 04:57.375
- Nothing.

04:57.375 --> 04:58.833
That's why I didn't
wanna talk about this.

04:58.833 --> 05:00.375
This is what I'm afraid of.
- What?

05:00.375 --> 05:01.958
Come on, dad, it's always
the same.

05:01.958 --> 05:03.291
It's always you and me
over here

05:03.291 --> 05:05.000
and Sam and mom over there.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.541
And, Sam, she'll just get mad

05:06.541 --> 05:08.375
if she thinks that
you're on my side.

05:08.375 --> 05:10.208
- I'm not taking sides.

05:10.208 --> 05:13.416
I want my girls to make up.
That's all.

05:13.416 --> 05:15.041
Let me speak to her.

05:15.041 --> 05:17.208
Sometimes a fight gets to a
point where you need a mediator.

05:17.208 --> 05:19.500
Someone with perspective.

05:19.500 --> 05:21.458
- I gotta get back to work.

05:21.458 --> 05:23.333
I love you, dad.
- I love you.

05:24.833 --> 05:27.333
- Thanks for the sandwich.

05:27.333 --> 05:30.500
(Elevator dings,
phones ringing)

05:30.500 --> 05:32.166
- You must have a horseshoe
tucked somewhere

05:32.166 --> 05:34.125
I don't wanna know about.

05:34.125 --> 05:36.750
But then again, maybe I do.

05:36.750 --> 05:38.250
- Brent, what is it?

05:38.250 --> 05:40.250
- Marcus Stahl is in
the hizouse.

05:40.250 --> 05:42.083
Not a moment too soon.

05:42.083 --> 05:44.541
- Oh, thank God.
Does Julianne know?

05:44.541 --> 05:47.291
- Mm-hmm.
- Good, thank you.

05:47.291 --> 05:49.291
- Ah, Mr. Stahl.

05:49.291 --> 05:51.125
- Mm, oh. Got your messages.

05:51.125 --> 05:52.666
Look, I'm sorry I didn't
get back to you sooner,

05:52.666 --> 05:54.125
but things have been
just, kind of crazy,

05:54.125 --> 05:55.958
with me working and thinking
and really

05:55.958 --> 05:57.375
trying to construct something.

05:57.375 --> 05:58.750
You know, I mean,
something good.

05:58.750 --> 06:00.208
- Of course, Of course.

06:00.208 --> 06:01.625
It's good to see you, you know?

06:01.625 --> 06:03.000
We really need those pages.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.541
- Mm-hmm. Yup.

06:04.541 --> 06:07.291
Oh, yes, the, um... the pages.

06:07.291 --> 06:09.166
- Yeah. I mean, to be honest,

06:09.166 --> 06:10.583
we were a getting little bit
worried,

06:10.583 --> 06:13.375
but now that you're here
it's, it's all good.

06:13.375 --> 06:16.166
You did, you did bring them
with you?

06:16.166 --> 06:19.041
- Nothing?! Nothing at all?
Not even one page?

06:19.041 --> 06:21.625
- I've been trying.

06:21.625 --> 06:24.000
Okay, I've been sitting
at my desk, but... I'm sorry.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.375
- Oh, oh, you're sorry.

06:26.375 --> 06:27.958
Well, that definitely takes
the sting out of the slap

06:27.958 --> 06:29.833
you just laid across my face.

06:29.833 --> 06:31.541
- Julianne, listen to me,

06:31.541 --> 06:36.791
it's not gonna happen,
you just... have to accept it.

06:36.791 --> 06:38.833
I'm walking away.

06:38.833 --> 06:41.500
- You promised us a book
we could have on the shelves
for Christmas.

06:41.500 --> 06:43.416
And we've put a lot of time,
resources,

06:43.416 --> 06:45.125
and a lot of money into this.

06:45.125 --> 06:47.708
So, no, I do not accept it.
And you just can't walk away.

06:47.708 --> 06:50.166
- Yes, I can.
- You cashed the advance.

06:50.166 --> 06:52.875
- I'll pay it back.
- And you'll be talking to our
lawyers, all ten of them.

06:52.875 --> 06:54.583
- Fine. Fine. You go ahead and
do whatever you want,

06:54.583 --> 06:56.541
But it's not gonna get
a goddamn book out of me!

06:56.541 --> 06:58.166
Because... I give up.

07:01.541 --> 07:04.458
(Teary breaths, welling up)
I can't...

07:06.375 --> 07:10.166
I can't go back there.
And I won't.

07:17.541 --> 07:20.375
- Well, you can't really type
in a straight jacket.

07:20.375 --> 07:22.416
Can't do coke in a straight
jacket, either.

07:24.416 --> 07:26.166
Mister Stahl.

07:26.166 --> 07:28.041
Please, I know that we just
freaked you out back there.

07:28.041 --> 07:30.125
- What is this?
Good cop, bad cop?

07:30.125 --> 07:31.000
- No, not at all.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.250
I just, I just came to tell you
that I think that I understand-

07:33.250 --> 07:34.541
- Oh, you understand?
- Yes.

07:34.541 --> 07:36.500
When you said that you can't
go back there,

07:36.500 --> 07:39.583
I mean, you meant to that
time in your life, right?

07:39.583 --> 07:42.625
- What are you, a shrink
slumming as someone's assistant?

07:42.625 --> 07:44.375
- You're absolutely right,

07:44.375 --> 07:46.083
I don't know what it's like
to struggle with an addiction,

07:46.083 --> 07:48.500
but I do know how painful
it can be to face the past.

07:50.750 --> 07:53.375
And sometimes the best way to
deal with something horrible

07:53.375 --> 07:57.125
that's happened to us, is...
is to revisit it.

07:57.125 --> 07:59.416
to take a really good,
long, hard look at it.

08:02.625 --> 08:05.708
I mean, that's just my opinion.

08:05.708 --> 08:08.333
And it's not just for
the good of the book,

08:08.333 --> 08:10.458
it's good for you.

08:16.208 --> 08:18.291
- When does Galvin need
the pages?

08:18.291 --> 08:22.000
- Um... Tonight.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.125
- I can't promise you anything.
- Of course.

08:25.583 --> 08:27.875
(Button clicks)

08:31.541 --> 08:34.125
- Dad, I'm sorry, but you can't
just come to my work

08:34.125 --> 08:36.416
and upset me like this.

08:36.416 --> 08:38.791
What happened between Erica and
I has nothing to do with you.

08:38.791 --> 08:41.750
- You're both my daughters, it
has everything to do with me.

08:41.750 --> 08:43.500
Your sister loves you,
I know you know that.

08:43.500 --> 08:45.041
And I know you also know,

08:45.041 --> 08:47.291
she'd never do purposely
anything hurt you.

08:47.291 --> 08:50.000
- Big surprise. You're siding
with her even now.

08:50.000 --> 08:51.750
- I am not siding with her.

08:51.750 --> 08:55.166
- Dad, she told me
not to marry my husband,

08:55.166 --> 08:57.166
she told me that
he doesn't love me,

08:57.166 --> 08:59.666
five minutes before I was about
to walk down the aisle.

08:59.666 --> 09:01.625
- I know.

09:01.625 --> 09:04.583
But your refusing to speak
to her is not the answer.

09:06.291 --> 09:09.000
What you're doing is hurting
you, I can see it in your face.

09:10.625 --> 09:12.291
You can't just give up
on your relationship.

09:12.291 --> 09:13.750
You have to, at the very least,

09:13.750 --> 09:15.208
try to understand
why she said it.

09:15.208 --> 09:18.208
- Okay, you did not
just suggest that?

09:18.208 --> 09:19.666
- Sam.
- No!

09:19.666 --> 09:22.208
I don't need to understand why.

09:22.208 --> 09:24.041
I don't need to talk about it.

09:24.041 --> 09:26.458
And if you keep bringing it up,

09:26.458 --> 09:28.541
we won't have anything left
to talk about, at all.

09:36.666 --> 09:38.083
- For the first time
in my professional career

09:38.083 --> 09:39.541
I have no idea what to do.

09:39.541 --> 09:41.458
- I do. We rain hellfire on him.

09:41.458 --> 09:43.083
We set Galvin's team of
soulless,

09:43.083 --> 09:44.666
baby-eating lawyers
on his neurotic ass.

09:44.666 --> 09:47.666
No. No lawyer, not even ours,

09:47.666 --> 09:49.291
can legally compel someone
to write a book

09:49.291 --> 09:51.541
that they don't wanna write.
We're cooked.

09:51.541 --> 09:53.458
- Stahl said he'd get me pages.

09:53.458 --> 09:55.541
- Oh my God, you are so naive.

09:55.541 --> 09:59.208
No, we gotta move on
to a back up plan.

09:59.208 --> 10:01.250
What about that lady,
the bag lady,

10:01.250 --> 10:02.666
who saved all the cats?

10:02.666 --> 10:04.125
- Dogs.
- Whatever.

10:04.125 --> 10:05.625
- For the Christmas book?

10:05.625 --> 10:07.541
- Ah... I mean, nothing says
Christmas like...

10:07.541 --> 10:09.666
little puppies being saved
from an uncertain fate.

10:09.666 --> 10:12.708
- Warms the cockles.
- That it does. Make it happen.

10:12.708 --> 10:14.208
- Julianne.
- Chuga-chuga-chuga-chuga,

10:14.208 --> 10:16.708
that's the sound
of the puppy train.

10:16.708 --> 10:18.833
And the train is leaving
the station, you might
wanna climb on.

10:18.833 --> 10:21.125
- Stahl's book, it's important,
it's hopeful and original--

10:21.125 --> 10:22.500
Hey, look. I know you're all
"invested"

10:22.500 --> 10:24.291
and I know this is your "baby",

10:24.291 --> 10:26.750
but it's not mine and it never
was, you're gonna let it go.

10:26.750 --> 10:29.083
- Mr. Galvin asked for pages.

10:29.083 --> 10:30.625
- Let me break it down for you.

10:30.625 --> 10:33.166
- You can either...
fix me a latte and drop this?

10:33.166 --> 10:34.625
Or you can keep fighting
this losing battle

10:34.625 --> 10:36.500
and go home for good.

10:38.333 --> 10:40.291
- Erica.
- (Frustrated moan)

10:40.291 --> 10:42.708
- A word? The word is hari-kari.

10:42.708 --> 10:44.625
Don't do it, because I like you

10:44.625 --> 10:47.166
and I want you to stay, okay?

10:47.166 --> 10:48.958
Look, everybody has a breaking
point,

10:48.958 --> 10:51.500
and Julianne just hit it.
You may be right about Stahl-

10:51.500 --> 10:53.708
- No, Brent, I know that I'm
right.

10:53.708 --> 10:55.458
- No, you don't.

10:55.458 --> 10:58.666
And even if you did? It's
either his book or your job.

10:58.666 --> 11:01.291
Give in, Erica. Stahl did.

11:03.291 --> 11:05.291
- Fine.
- Good. I'm happy.

11:08.875 --> 11:10.666
Go make Julianne that latte,

11:10.666 --> 11:12.416
and ask her if she needs
help with that...

11:12.416 --> 11:15.333
bag lady/dog-memoir-thingy.
Okay?

11:18.083 --> 11:20.041
(Sighs)

11:20.041 --> 11:22.375
(Startled exhale)

11:26.291 --> 11:28.500
(Dr. Tom sighs)

11:30.333 --> 11:31.750
- You just gonna stand there?

11:31.750 --> 11:33.666
- Yes, I am. Because, uh...

11:33.666 --> 11:36.500
we're not doing this today.

11:36.500 --> 11:38.791
- "You can complain because
roses have thorns

11:38.791 --> 11:41.666
or you can rejoice because
thorns have roses."

11:41.666 --> 11:43.750
Zig Ziglar.
- Yeah, who's he?

11:43.750 --> 11:45.875
- Oh, God, I don't know.
I have no idea.

11:45.875 --> 11:47.750
The quote stuck though.

11:49.250 --> 11:52.416
Wow. You look tired.

11:52.416 --> 11:53.666
I am tired.

11:53.666 --> 11:56.000
My entire life is a mess.
my sister won't talk to me,

11:56.000 --> 11:58.291
"thank you" for that.
My boss wants to fire me,

11:58.291 --> 12:01.166
because God forbid
I actually have an opinion.

12:01.166 --> 12:03.541
And now here you are.

12:03.541 --> 12:05.916
But you know what, Dr. Tom?
I'm not doing it.

12:05.916 --> 12:08.750
Our therapy has been
a big step back,

12:08.750 --> 12:11.250
So the last thing I wanna do to
top off this crap-tacular day

12:11.250 --> 12:13.166
is a session. Believe me.

12:14.666 --> 12:16.625
- You done?

12:16.625 --> 12:18.208
- With all this? Yes, I am.

12:19.833 --> 12:21.541
- Well, where are you going?
- Back to work.

12:21.541 --> 12:24.416
- Oh, so you're gonna give up
then? (door rattles)

12:24.416 --> 12:26.875
- Well, it, uh, it seems
to be going around.

