26:50.125 --> 26:52.708
to pay for them.

26:52.708 --> 26:54.875
- Hey look, Sam, I'll, uh...
I'll buy you a new pair--

26:54.875 --> 26:56.708
- I don't want a new pair!
I want this pair.

26:56.708 --> 26:58.125
And I'd rather walk around
barefoot

26:58.125 --> 26:59.500
than wear those things.

26:59.500 --> 27:03.333
- Looks like somebody
needs to cool off.

27:03.333 --> 27:05.250
- Don't even think about it.

27:07.125 --> 27:09.791
Flick me again and I'll--

27:09.791 --> 27:12.166
Erica, I am warning you.
- No, that wasn't a flick.

27:12.166 --> 27:14.208
You said a flick,
that was a splash.

27:14.208 --> 27:15.708
- Oh, I will show you a splash.

27:15.708 --> 27:18.458
- (Screams)

27:18.458 --> 27:20.083
(Playful screams)

27:23.583 --> 27:25.375
(Water splashes, playful yelps)

27:27.416 --> 27:32.750
♪ ♪

27:32.750 --> 27:35.416
(Train whistle toots,
train rattles by)

27:39.291 --> 27:40.666
- Man, I am so hungry right now!

27:40.666 --> 27:42.375
- Oh, me too.

27:42.375 --> 27:44.208
Do you remember where they
have those little donuts?

27:44.208 --> 27:46.666
- That's the C.N.E.
Funnel cakes?

27:46.666 --> 27:48.958
- Funnel cakes, I love funnel
cakes.

27:48.958 --> 27:51.375
- Do you know who really loves
funnel cakes?

27:51.375 --> 27:53.541
- Leo. Let's go find him
- Okay.

27:55.833 --> 27:58.416
Both: Woooo! (Giggling)

28:00.916 --> 28:02.708
Tina: (playful giggle)
No, Tiger.

28:04.750 --> 28:07.791
If I get caught skipping out
on the mini-golf?

28:07.791 --> 28:10.333
My career is basically over.

28:10.333 --> 28:13.416
- Well... my motto, Tina?
- Mm-hm.

28:13.416 --> 28:15.500
- Live each day like
it's your last.

28:17.166 --> 28:19.333
- I think I'm gonna get that
tattooed on my back.

28:19.333 --> 28:20.750
(Giggles)

28:23.000 --> 28:25.750
Sam: You don't think he can
actually be at the nude beach,
do you?

28:25.750 --> 28:27.791
- Well, I know that we're not
gonna go to find out.

28:27.791 --> 28:29.750
I mean, today's been bad enough
without seeing that.

28:29.750 --> 28:31.583
- Well, we can't go back
to the city without him,

28:31.583 --> 28:33.583
so, what do we do?

28:33.583 --> 28:36.875
- (Inhales) You know what? If...

28:36.875 --> 28:39.458
if being with Tina
makes Leo happy today,

28:39.458 --> 28:41.291
let's just let him
be with Tina.

28:41.291 --> 28:43.916
But you keep talking about
the ferry and sunset.

28:43.916 --> 28:46.916
- Well, then it'll just be
you and I, total sister time,

28:46.916 --> 28:48.625
if that's cool with you.

28:48.625 --> 28:51.208
- Of course. Why would you
even ask?

28:51.208 --> 28:52.708
- Well, because of the shoes,

28:52.708 --> 28:54.333
you know, I thought that
you might still be mad.

28:54.333 --> 28:55.916
- Well, I'm not happy, but...

28:55.916 --> 28:59.333
I don't hold grudges,
you know that.

28:59.333 --> 29:01.416
Can I have one of these?
I wanna souvenir.

29:01.416 --> 29:03.333
- Sam, we, uh, we live
in Toronto.

29:03.333 --> 29:05.500
- Yeah, but I wanna remember
today.

29:05.500 --> 29:07.625
- Thanks. There you go.

29:07.625 --> 29:09.625
- Thank you.
- May you always...

29:09.625 --> 29:11.791
think of our incredible
afternoon together, Sam.

29:13.291 --> 29:15.875
(Snow globe sloshes)

29:15.875 --> 29:17.750
(Small laugh)

29:22.250 --> 29:25.750
- Tina, you are the bomb.

29:25.750 --> 29:28.708
- You're not so bad yourself,
Tiger.

29:28.708 --> 29:30.500
- (Breathless laugh) I, uh...
I have a confession to make.

29:32.041 --> 29:34.958
My name's not Tiger, it's Leo.

29:34.958 --> 29:36.833
- It's Leo the lion?
That's even better.

29:38.708 --> 29:40.625
Leo: (small moan) Whoa.

29:43.666 --> 29:45.750
Incoming roid rage
at four o'clock.

29:45.750 --> 29:47.958
- Whoops.
- Oh, you know him?

29:47.958 --> 29:50.708
- Um... That would be Alex.
That's my boyfriend.

29:54.916 --> 29:56.958
- Oh my God! Oh my God,
oh my God!

29:56.958 --> 29:59.625
- Baby. Baby. No, baby, no, no!
No, baby, don't!

30:02.541 --> 30:05.041
Sam: Yup, Leo is definitely
at the nude beach.

30:05.041 --> 30:07.041
- No problemo, it's not
the last ferry.

30:07.041 --> 30:08.875
Just the last ferry
with the best view ever.

30:10.375 --> 30:12.541
Leo: Run for it!

30:12.541 --> 30:15.666
Tina: Alex! Alex, chill!
It's not that big of a deal!

30:15.666 --> 30:17.166
Leo: Erica, hurry up!

30:17.166 --> 30:18.916
- Hey! Leave my brother alone,
you got it?

30:18.916 --> 30:20.875
(Hard slap, Alex grunts)

30:20.875 --> 30:22.208
Don't mess with the babysitter.

30:23.833 --> 30:25.916
(Heavy breaths)
- That girl just-- (Slap)

30:25.916 --> 30:28.500
Amber told me that you
made out with Tiffany
from the whack-a-mole.

30:28.500 --> 30:30.791
Now you know how it feels!

30:30.791 --> 30:33.458
- Oh, honey. Are you okay?
- No.

30:34.958 --> 30:37.208
- (Laughs, panting)

30:37.208 --> 30:38.625
- Leo, are you okay?

30:38.625 --> 30:40.791
- I'm cool.

30:40.791 --> 30:42.416
Let me tell you, sis?

30:42.416 --> 30:45.708
You rocked hard.

30:45.708 --> 30:47.416
Good day.

30:47.416 --> 30:50.625
- Great day.
- Perfect day.

30:50.625 --> 30:52.833
♪ Sun is gonna shine ♪
(Sun is gonna shine)

30:54.333 --> 30:56.375
♪ Sun is gonna shine ♪

30:56.375 --> 30:58.416
♪ When the rain is done ♪

30:58.416 --> 31:01.458
♪ Sun is gonna shine ♪

31:03.375 --> 31:07.625
♪ Oh, sun is gonna shine ♪

31:10.416 --> 31:12.500
♪ When the rain is done ♪

31:12.500 --> 31:16.500
♪ Sun is gonna shine ♪

31:16.500 --> 31:18.625
♪ Sun is gonna shine
When the rain is done ♪

31:23.458 --> 31:25.708
(Leo laughs, front door shuts)

31:25.708 --> 31:27.625
- Mom, dad, you should have
been there.

31:27.625 --> 31:29.416
We had such a fun day.

31:31.041 --> 31:32.750
- I'm glad someone
had a great day.

31:32.750 --> 31:36.041
(Photo album slaps shut)

31:36.041 --> 31:37.791
(Retreating footsteps)

31:43.583 --> 31:45.500
- Do you guys think...

31:45.500 --> 31:47.583
mom and dad are gonna get
divorced?

31:47.583 --> 31:49.625
- No. No, they're just...

31:51.916 --> 31:54.916
they're just going through
a rough patch.

31:54.916 --> 31:57.666
- We know that's not true.

31:59.666 --> 32:01.791
But it'll be okay, Sam.

32:03.875 --> 32:05.958
- No, it will.

32:05.958 --> 32:09.958
Our parents may be psycho,
but I'm not going anywhere.

32:12.125 --> 32:14.958
Neither is Erica, right?

32:14.958 --> 32:18.166
- You got it.

32:18.166 --> 32:20.833
Well, I don't know about you
guys, but I am starving

32:20.833 --> 32:23.000
'cause I left everything
I ate on the island.

32:26.333 --> 32:27.750
(Wrapper crinkles)

32:29.291 --> 32:30.791
(Startled gasps)
- Oh my God.

32:30.791 --> 32:32.666
Do not sneak up on me
like that ever again.

32:32.666 --> 32:34.958
- Sorry, I was just about
to make Julianne her latte.

32:34.958 --> 32:37.916
- Yeah uh, Julianne doesn't
take drain cleaner in her latte.

32:37.916 --> 32:40.000
- Um, hey, Brent.

32:40.000 --> 32:41.916
How long has it been since,
um, we last talked there?

32:43.541 --> 32:45.041
Why are you looking
at me like that?

32:45.041 --> 32:47.458
- I'm just trying to see
if you're having a seizure.

32:47.458 --> 32:49.083
Do you smell burnt toast?

32:49.083 --> 32:51.708
- Look, Brent, I need you
to cover for me.

32:51.708 --> 32:53.958
- No, you need to bring
Julianne her latte.

32:53.958 --> 32:55.583
She's thirsty and cranky.

32:55.583 --> 32:56.958
And I need to speak
to the art department

32:56.958 --> 32:58.291
About a cover for the cat lady
book.

32:58.291 --> 33:01.250
- Dog lady book.
- Whatever.

33:01.250 --> 33:03.083
Mm, my God, my Kung Fu
is strong.

33:03.083 --> 33:04.625
- Look, I'm sure it is,
but, Brent,

33:04.625 --> 33:06.250
You need to cover for me, okay?
'cause there's something--

33:06.250 --> 33:08.625
- You haven't said anything
I said earlier, did you?

33:08.625 --> 33:10.541
- No, I did. And I should
probably follow your advice,

33:10.541 --> 33:12.125
but I'm not really thinking
with my head right now.

33:12.125 --> 33:14.041
Please, come on, come on,
please-please-please.

33:16.000 --> 33:17.666
- If things turns out the way
I think they will,

33:17.666 --> 33:19.458
I call dibs on your ergonomic
chair.

33:19.458 --> 33:21.541
And your orchids.

33:21.541 --> 33:24.583
And your colored paper clips!
- Okay.

33:29.375 --> 33:31.791
Hello?!

33:31.791 --> 33:34.625
Mr. Stahl?

33:34.625 --> 33:38.291
Um, um, it's Erica Strange
from River Rock Publishing.

33:38.291 --> 33:40.833
I just, I let myself in,
I hope that's okay?

33:42.291 --> 33:44.041
Mr. Stahl?

33:44.041 --> 33:46.208
I-I just, uh...

33:46.208 --> 33:50.125
Came over to see if you needed
any help with the manuscript?

33:50.125 --> 33:51.500
Hello?!

33:53.875 --> 33:55.750
(Folder crinkles)

33:55.750 --> 33:57.750
(Shocked gasp)

33:57.750 --> 34:00.625
What do you mean you haven't
written anything?

34:00.625 --> 34:03.041
There's gotta be four chapters
here.

34:03.041 --> 34:04.833
Mr. Stahl, I knew that
you could do it,

34:04.833 --> 34:06.583
I knew that you could face...

34:11.625 --> 34:13.875
Mr. Stahl?

34:13.875 --> 34:15.500
Marcus!

34:17.000 --> 34:18.833
Oh God. Marcus!

34:20.250 --> 34:21.958
Marcus.

34:21.958 --> 34:24.083
Marcus, can you hear me?

34:26.875 --> 34:28.875
(Keypad beeps)

34:28.875 --> 34:31.833
Marcus. Marcus.

34:31.833 --> 34:35.208
Oh, shit. Oh, shit-shit-shit.

34:35.708 --> 34:37.875
It's 459 Arbour Street.

34:37.875 --> 34:40.458
I think he may have overdosed.

34:40.458 --> 34:43.333
There was-I mean, there was
cocaine and pills and, I, I...

34:43.333 --> 34:46.166
I forgot how to do all this
stuff, just please hurry.

34:46.166 --> 34:48.250
Mr. Stahl, please wake up.

34:48.250 --> 34:50.125
(Hard slap, stunned gasp)

34:50.125 --> 34:52.666
Oh God, he's awake. He's...

34:52.666 --> 34:55.708
Oh God. Oh, thank God.
- (Coughs)

34:57.416 --> 35:00.166
- (Heavy breathing, coughs)
- Marcus. It's okay.

35:00.166 --> 35:02.083
You're gonna be okay.

35:02.083 --> 35:04.500
(Gurney rattles)

35:17.833 --> 35:19.708
(Half laughs to herself)

35:22.916 --> 35:26.208
(Pen clicks)
- Sam.

35:26.208 --> 35:28.750
Hey, Sam. Wait-wait.
Hey, just talk to me.

35:28.750 --> 35:31.000
- What are you doing here?
Because I told dad earlier--

35:31.000 --> 35:33.125
- No, no, one of our authors,
he overdosed.

35:33.125 --> 35:34.791
- Oh. I'm sorry to hear that.

35:36.666 --> 35:39.000
- Oh, come on, Sam,
we're sisters.

35:39.000 --> 35:40.750
Are we, are we really
never gonna to talk again?

35:40.750 --> 35:42.875
- Exactly, Erica, we're sisters.

35:42.875 --> 35:45.291
We are supposed to love each
other and support each other--

35:45.291 --> 35:47.208
- And forgive each other.

35:49.958 --> 35:52.833
- Do you still feel
the same way about Josh?

35:52.833 --> 35:55.458
- Yes.
- Then I can't forgive you.

35:57.041 --> 35:58.833
It's simple, you forced me
to choose

35:58.833 --> 36:00.791
between my sister and
my husband

36:00.791 --> 36:02.375
and I made my choice.

36:02.375 --> 36:04.625
- I didn't ask you to choose.

36:08.083 --> 36:10.250
So, that's it?

36:10.250 --> 36:12.125
- That's it.

36:13.583 --> 36:15.208
- Fine.

36:17.166 --> 36:19.916
Hey, Sam.

36:19.916 --> 36:21.875
When the day comes
that you do need me,

36:21.875 --> 36:24.916
and it will come,
I'll be there for you.

36:24.916 --> 36:27.125
Say what you want,
you're my sister.

36:27.125 --> 36:29.958
We've lost Leo
and I refuse to lose you.

36:37.333 --> 36:44.083
♪ ♪

36:44.083 --> 36:46.166
- Rehab again.

36:47.750 --> 36:50.041
- Is there anything
that I can do?

36:50.041 --> 36:52.250
- Well, don't you think
you've done enough?

36:53.750 --> 36:55.958
(Both half laugh)

36:55.958 --> 36:58.041
- Don't worry, I'll be fine.

37:00.083 --> 37:03.250
Look, I've done it before,
I can do it again.

37:03.250 --> 37:05.708
Only this time, I'll be busier.

37:08.333 --> 37:10.916
I have a book to write.

37:10.916 --> 37:12.625
- Mm-hmm.

37:12.625 --> 37:14.583
- (Chuckles)

37:16.708 --> 37:19.125
Thank you.

37:22.166 --> 37:25.083
- So, she didn't make my latte?
And she didn't go home?

37:25.083 --> 37:28.083
She went to Stahl's house?
What, to hold his hand?

37:28.083 --> 37:30.333
- Until he finished
the first chapters.

37:30.333 --> 37:32.250
- Why?! We don't want
his writing!

37:32.250 --> 37:34.208
We want the goddamn cat lady!

37:34.208 --> 37:37.250
- Dog lady.
- Whatever.

37:37.250 --> 37:38.875
(Nervous exhale) Frank.

37:38.875 --> 37:40.208
Just the man I was hoping
to see.

37:40.208 --> 37:43.041
- Julianne, Stahl's pages?

37:43.041 --> 37:46.041
We agreed they would be
on my desk by day's end, yes?

37:46.041 --> 37:48.166
- Uh, Stahl has... stalled.

37:50.041 --> 37:52.375
- What happened?

37:52.375 --> 37:55.375
- An old habit reappeared,
if you know what I mean.

37:55.375 --> 37:57.250
- Frank. Frank, I...

37:59.250 --> 38:01.333
I have prepared an incredible
plan b.

38:03.041 --> 38:04.833
And I'm, I'm stoked.

38:04.833 --> 38:06.791
I have some excellent ideas
for the cover

38:06.791 --> 38:10.208
of our new feel good
Christmas title, okay?

38:10.208 --> 38:13.375
(Clears throat)
Imagine a grubby hand reaching
into a fire

38:13.375 --> 38:15.541
to pull out fuzzy little
kittens...

38:15.541 --> 38:18.375
- I got 'em! Stahl's pages.
And they're good.

38:18.375 --> 38:21.125
(Stammers) They're very good.

38:21.125 --> 38:24.208
- From what I hear, the man's
in no condition to write.

38:24.208 --> 38:27.916
- Um, which is why he's, uh...
going off to rehab, sir.

38:27.916 --> 38:30.416
Rehab? Oh, do you really think
that's gonna make us feel all
peachy?

38:30.416 --> 38:33.125
It should because he's...
he's facing his problems.

38:33.125 --> 38:35.958
- Fab, but I told you,
we're moving on.

38:35.958 --> 38:37.916
- Please, please don't give up
on this.

38:37.916 --> 38:39.833
- Erica, drop it.

38:39.833 --> 38:42.250
- Mr. Galvin, you know... Stahl.

38:42.250 --> 38:44.541
And I mean, he is not a quitter.

38:44.541 --> 38:46.291
I mean, his whole life
has proven that.

38:46.291 --> 38:48.416
And he, he just told me,
he promised me,

38:48.416 --> 38:51.500
that he will come out
of rehab with a book,

38:51.500 --> 38:54.333
if you could please
just take a look at this.

38:54.333 --> 38:56.250
You'll see, it's...
it's really good.

39:01.416 --> 39:03.375
- Well, we can't risk depending
on Stahl's book,

39:03.375 --> 39:05.375
and having it not come through.

39:05.375 --> 39:07.000
Christmas is our big season,
my dear,

39:07.000 --> 39:08.958
And we can't be left
holding the bag.

39:11.333 --> 39:13.916
That's why we're gonna develop
both books concurrently.

39:13.916 --> 39:15.458
Julianne.
- But, Frank.

39:15.458 --> 39:17.291
Put someone on the dog lady.

39:17.291 --> 39:18.750
If Stahl's book is ready
in time,

39:18.750 --> 39:20.583
it becomes a Christmas launch,
if not,

39:20.583 --> 39:23.583
dog lady takes its place.

39:23.583 --> 39:27.375
You're right.
Stahl isn't a quitter.

39:27.375 --> 39:29.958
If he was, we wouldn't be
doing a book about him.

39:29.958 --> 39:32.750
- Frank?
- Make it happen, Julianne.

39:35.500 --> 39:37.708
- Thank you, Mr. Galvin.

39:41.416 --> 39:43.166
(Relieved exhales)

39:50.500 --> 39:51.875
Would you like a latte?

39:53.541 --> 39:56.166
- Look at you. You could get
a job at Starbucks.

39:56.166 --> 39:58.208
- Yeah, well, I might have to
if they hate Stahl's writing,

39:58.208 --> 40:00.625
but I just, I couldn't let go.

40:00.625 --> 40:02.958
I couldn't give up.
- Oh, you could.

40:02.958 --> 40:05.291
- I almost did, but it wouldn't
be right.

40:05.291 --> 40:07.958
- Mm. Oh.

40:07.958 --> 40:10.083
- How much do they pay
at Starbucks, anyways?

40:10.083 --> 40:12.333
- "We can not, we will not,
choose the path of surrender."

40:12.333 --> 40:14.125
Woodrow T. Wilson.

40:15.750 --> 40:17.458
- I, uh, I checked the temp
on the espresso

40:17.458 --> 40:19.458
and the milk is extra hot.

40:19.458 --> 40:21.375
- I read Stahl's chapters,
Erica.

40:23.083 --> 40:24.625
- Wow, that was, uh,
that was fast.

40:24.625 --> 40:26.958
- Well, Frank demanded it.

40:26.958 --> 40:29.625
And turns out you're right,
they're not bad.

40:29.625 --> 40:31.833
- Oh? Well, that,
I mean, that's great.

40:33.458 --> 40:36.541
Okay, do not let what I'm about
to say go to your head.

40:36.541 --> 40:39.166
- I promise.

40:39.166 --> 40:41.666
- I'm impressed.

40:41.666 --> 40:43.500
You have fought for a property
that you cared about,

40:43.500 --> 40:45.333
despite all the nay-sayers.

40:45.333 --> 40:47.625
And... you were right to.

40:47.625 --> 40:50.458
Stahl needs more time,
he'll get it.

40:50.458 --> 40:52.541
Hmm.

40:52.541 --> 40:53.833
(Sips latte and groans)

40:55.375 --> 40:58.208
This makes me less impressed.

40:58.208 --> 41:00.083
- (Clears throat) Right.

41:04.541 --> 41:06.541
Hi, Ryan, it's me.

41:06.541 --> 41:08.500
Um... listen, I'm sorry
about earlier.

41:08.500 --> 41:10.875
Uh, tomorrow night sounds great.

41:10.875 --> 41:12.541
And... (deep inhale)

41:12.541 --> 41:14.375
I hope that you're
having fun with Josh

41:14.375 --> 41:16.083
and give me a call.

41:16.083 --> 41:18.541
Oh!

41:18.541 --> 41:19.958
(Surprised gasp)

41:22.208 --> 41:23.833
- Heirloom tomatoes.
My secret weapon.

41:25.375 --> 41:28.083
- Um... how did you get
in here?

41:28.083 --> 41:31.125
- I bribed your building manager
with promises of leftovers.

41:31.125 --> 41:32.625
(Timer dings)

41:32.625 --> 41:34.000
- Oh, crap, my pine nuts
are burning.

41:34.000 --> 41:36.333
- (Laughs)

41:36.333 --> 41:38.833
So, what happened
to your plans with Josh?

41:40.250 --> 41:43.750
- (French accent) I called him,
told him I changed my mind.

41:43.750 --> 41:45.583
And then I tried to think
of this creative way

41:45.583 --> 41:47.916
to make it up to you.

41:47.916 --> 41:50.333
- Mmm, well...

41:50.333 --> 41:52.875
Uh, the apron? Did the trick.

41:56.583 --> 41:58.875
♪ Leaving with this weight
on my shoulders ♪

42:00.541 --> 42:04.333
Erica: They say the greatest
mistake is giving up.

42:04.333 --> 42:07.125
That true strength lies
in the will to keep trying.

42:10.750 --> 42:12.583
Keep hoping things will
get better.

42:15.458 --> 42:16.875
